  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To ensure provision of health services in areas affected by natural disasters, mass causality incidences and diseases outbreaks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to ensure life-saving trauma care, primary healthcare, nutrition and WASH services are provided effectively in hard to reach and underserved areas. This WHO project trains 650 HCWs on early detection and reporting of COVID-19, trains contact tracing team on tracing contacts of confirmed COVID-19 cases, provides PPE kits, hand &amp; respiratory hygiene materials, and other needed supplies to Rapid Response Teams, conducts public awareness campaign on local radio in high risk areas, supports of four blood banks with equipment, and equips six hospitals for Emergency Triage Assessment and Treatment (ETAT) among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 304,000 people, including 27,500 women, 56,500 men, over 200,000 children, and 8,310 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
